caption: Had a ball for Naje's birthday.

The filet was cooked perfectly, and all the appetizers and sides were amazing. Our server, John, suggested a wonderful red Pinot Noir. I don't have a Morton's where I live, so whenever I'm in town visiting family, Morton's is a must. Thanks, John, for making our dinner such an enjoyable experience!
I went there for my tenth anniversary they made us feel like we were the only ones there. Food was great. I give them 10 🌟.

We had dinner on Friday, I thought the food would have been a lot for the price. The steaks were tender but taste was lacking. The drinks we ordered was made wrong and not with what was requested. I definitely won't eat there again the next time I'm in Louisville!

We had an excellent dining experience at Morton’s on March 11. Everything was delicious from appetizers to dessert. Per our servers recommendation, we ordered the bacon steak appetizer which was absolutely amazing. Our server went above and beyond to make our experience great. We will be returning and requesting a table with John from Minnesota.

Very elegant and romantic setting. Good music in the background and the staff is the best. Delicious steaks, but has some strong chard flavor. Very pricey. You will spend a at least $150 on a dinner for 2.
Best stake and service

Tonight was our first time dining at Morton’s. I had mentioned it was our anniversary in the reservation notes, and they went above and beyond to help us celebrate! The food was top notch and the service was amazing. We felt very welcomed and safe with all the Covid-19 protocol in place. Highly recommend for any celebration or nice dining occasion. We will be back!
Steak and drinks were really good. The sides weren't that great. Service was EXCELLENT!

Went for birthday meal. Staff very attentive,  despite group of 30+ in a bourbon tasting group nearby.  Food that was not hot was immediately warmed to my satisfaction. (Spinach side). The steak (great) and shellfish (scallops and shellfish) also great! Wine appears to average about $100 per bottle at the low end, so make sure you have "resources" to pay the check at the end of the evening!

The food was delicious. Service was great. Very nice romantic atmosphere. Large wine selection. My one complaint would have to be the pricing. Just a bit overpriced for me, considering I’ve had great steaks at other places for half the price.

The host was very rude I ask could I have my food reheated because I was late picking it up, and the host acted like she had an attitude in doing so! I will never order from this restaurant again need better host and greeters!
ROBBY AND ALEX WERE THE BEST SERVERS IVE EVER HAD. I FELT LIKE ROYALTY ON MY 23RD BIRTHDAY
Graham made our experience absolutely incredible. Had never been here before but will definitely be back.
Great experience and marvelous food
First time at Morton's and everything was delicious! Steak, Lobster, Shrimp, Crab Cakes and Lobster Macaroni and Cheese we're all Hot and Delicious!!!

Great food and environment . May be the best servers that have ever served me. They used teamwork and made sure we were good at all times. It’s pricey but delicious . Top 3 steak in Louisville . I had the New York strip with Gouda potatoes au gratin . My girl got the steak and lobster Oscar. We had the bacon wrapped mozzarella for appetizer and the 3 scoop sundae was a complimentary dessert for my birthday . All the food was delicious
Best bone-in ribeye I've ever had. I'm a huge sauce lover and this steak needed nothing.

My husband and I are visiting Louisville from Chicago, we heard great things about Morton’s and our visit started out great. However, we waited over an hour ina half for our food and when we received it my husbands steak was cold and my burger bun was so burnt it was hard. The server we originally started with wasn’t very attentive or sympathetic. Very disappointed in our experience. Was most definitely not worth $200
Awesome  Filet oscar
Amazing
Excellent.
Great atmosphere. Great food

Ordered thru door dash to hotel. Food was cold and my 75 dollar steak tasted rancid/rotten like it's been in the fridge to long which was a complete bummer since I was looking forward to trying this steakhouse. Yes I understand I shouldn't have gotten it delivered to give it a shot but if that's the case don't offer it...oh and had no forks or knife or anything for that matter to eat any of it with. Luckily the hotel did. Everything else was great. Just highly disappointed in the porterhouse.

Was in town for the night.  Ordered steak for pickup for me and wife.  It was sitting on bar the entire time I was standing there waiting to be assisted.  Three ladies working bar area basically running around disorganized.  Finally was asked if I been helped....uh no I've been trying to get assistance for about 10min.  Yep as suspected that was my bag sitting there getting cold.  Asked about utensils since I'm staying at a hotel.  She responded yep there in the bag... which was sealed.  Get back to my room and there's no utensils in bag, food slightly warm, and both steaks overcooked.  Flavor and quality of the steaks were good besides being overdone.  Wouldn't recommend for the money. Service was very lacking. Going to Jeff Ruby's next time.
Great food great place.

It was sooo the Best steak, service, atmosphere (we were in a separate room business meeting). 8oz filet perfectly done to my request of med rare, sides enough to share 1-3 people, my glass was never empty of water, new utensils for each serving, ahi tuna appetizer was excellent! Parking was tricky to find a spot, valet is available, creme brulee oh my so wonderful! Pricey, but worth a nice evening dinner out!
The food was incredible. Our server was amazing as well. I loved the atmosphere. Overall a great experience.

Me and my boyfriend went to this place Friday night to celebrate our anniversary. We had a long day at work, and wanted to unwind and celebrate with a nice bottle of wine . My boyfriend has been to this place before, but it was my first time . Worst experience ever. My boyfriend was being friendly and just talking to the hostess about how we had just moved up the street, and that we’ve tried all of the restaurants in the area, but he hasn’t been to this one in a while and he wanted me to try it . The hostess basically rolled his eyes and told him that he would get us seated shortly. We waited for about 10 minutes, and a table next to the bar became available so we sat there until we could get a regular table . My boyfriend told the bartender that he already knew what kind of wine he wanted and to go ahead and bring it to us, so we could drink it while waiting for our table . She said ok, then my boyfriend asked the hostess how much longer it would be for our table and he said one would be available shortly because they were at their max capacity. So we continued to wait at the table by the bar . While thinking we were waiting on a bottle of wine, apparently the hostess and bartender got together and complained to the general manager about serving us alcohol.  She came to our table and told us that she was happy to seat us but we couldn’t have any alcohol because the staff were “concerned “ like are you kidding me ? The staff couldn’t handle someone talking to them and having a normal conversation? My boyfriend told the general manager that we haven’t drank in almost 6 weeks because we were getting into health and working out, so he didn’t drank a drop of liquor that night. She looked him up and down and said “congratulations but like I said, no alcohol “. Me and him just looked at each other very confused. I was just over it at the point and said it’s fine let’s just go get seated and order dinner. We sat down and the waitress gave us menus , then I saw the hostess walk over and whisper something in his ear . I’m assuming he told him not to serve us alcohol too since the waitress didn’t bother giving us a wine list . At that point we were both embarrassed and felt completely unwelcome and just decided to leave . The rude hostess didn’t say have a good night or anything. He just looked at us sideways with a smirk like he was glad we were leaving. We ended up going to Jeff Ruby’s up the street and felt WAY more welcome. The food was great and they were happy to serve us the 2 bottles of wine that we ordered, one was to take home .I will NEVER spend my money or allow my boyfriend to spend his in this place EVER!! We ordered a well worth it $730 meal at Jeff Ruby’s , where we were appreciated ! Too bad Morton’s lost a great potential regular customer. I’d give zero stars if I could.
Went for my wife's 50th Birthday; they made it so special for her!! I can't thank the staff and our waitress Debbie enough! And the filet mignon is an experience unlike any other in Louisville!

This place NEVER disappoints. Their stuck, no matter the cut is cooked to perfection. This is a meal I make a reservation for, don't eat all day, then enjoy every bite like it's my last. Morton's  is THE steak house!!!!
Cool place to meet and catch up with coworkers. Bring your hunger - portions are large. Reminds me of a place in New York I liked to visit.
Excellent food and excellent service. Probably the best steak in the city!
We drove here from Indianapolis since the Indy location is close and I'm glad we did everything we had a delicious and cooked to perfection

I've been here before, and I liked it better then.  I'm not sure the steak was all that different than I make at home.  Maybe COVID-19 has affected it. Still great food and service. Birthday cheesecake was delicious!  $300 for 4 people seems a bit high, but that was with tip.

Went here for our 4 year wedding anniversary, service was awesome, food was great, and for whatever the reason we had the entire place to ourselves. Personalized menus for the occasion.  5 stars because I can't give 10!
The stakes in this house is amazing, the atmosphere is great. Little pricey but it's worth it.
My first time, was their for a birthday dinner, the table was setup so nice, menu had the person name on it and the food was delicious! Nice place will go back!!
Food was delicious and the service was great! Will be returning, worth the money!
Stop by for dessert, both were delicious and worth the wait. The Expresso martini was an added bonus. Great service and  friendly staff
Dinner was so good! Great experience and even better service, thanks Robbie!
Great food, fantastic service
Best steak I've had in a longtime, maybe ever
Pork chop was superb and our waiter, Robbie, was absolutely amazing. Thank you!!!
This was a special occasion and the staff made it special and memorable. We plan to return in the future.
Very nice and 6 ft between tables
Best in town
Terrible experience for my 50th Birthday 🎂 The cooks were banging pot's and pan's being loud as possible to get us to leave...
Best steak ever!!!!
Great

Tiffany was an excellent server. She attended to everything from start to finish . Her personality made us feel at home. The food was magnificent and the atmosphere was also wonderful. Elegant yet cozy.
Really enjoyed myself... Food was amazing.. Employees were very friendly.
Rely nice!
Food was excellent , but service was poor only 6 tables in use and they messed up our salid and our stake order.
The service is phenomenal, I cannot deny that. However, after paying $79 for an slightly above average tasting steak, I cannot say I got my money’s worth.

During these hard times Morton’s has really stepped out offering excellent service (our waiter Graham was so attentive to give us a wonderful experience and he was extremely careful with cleanliness) and the food was delicious!
All around amazing dining experience, even the carryout was fantastic.  It is very pricey but they sometimes run specials for holiday events like mothers day etc.
Not a everyday place you can eat at but great for a special occasion.
Delicious as always! Amazing customer service once again!

We were in town this Memorial Day weekend visiting family. We were staying downtown and decided to look up some restaurants to catch an early dinner. My husband and I called Morton's to see if they were open and to see if we needed to make a reservation. We were told no and that they have seats available.  Upon arrival we were greeted by a Brian who was so uninviting.  He sat us in the back of the restaurant by the bar and when we asked if we could have a table in the actual dining area we were told they were full. Mind you there was only us and 1 other couple in the WHOLE restaurant. When we told him that we were gonna leave because of how we are being treated he just looked at us and answered a phone call. When he answered we over heard him say our first reservation is a 8 pm. How ironic is that when we arrived at 5pm. We feel that we were judged off our "Looks" as soon as we walked through the door. So just know if you look like US you may not get the same treatment as the next person.
By far the worst experience I've had in a restaurant. We were in there maybe 5 minutes before leaving. Brian was extremely rude!!! I will never visit this place again.
Was absolutely incredible

very late grubhub delivery: i found the cost of the filet outrageous . . . the 6 oz. cut was good, but certainly not outstanding . . . and there were no sides . . . for nearly 30 dollars i would have thought a potato or veg side would be automatically included. the shrimp were lovely.

While I have dined at other Morton's locations, this was my first time at this one. I'd become aware of an advertised "deal" on a three-course meal from a limited menu but the real draw was the bottle of Daou "The Pessimist" at $36.00! I couldn't resist it. So made a reservation and was joined by a friend. It was a Sunday evening so parking on the street right in front of the restaurant was available and free. Upon entering the building, I was surprised to discover the restaurant was down a level in what I would usually think of as the "basement". It required going down a flight of narrow and somewhat steep stairs. If there was an elevator, I didn't see it. We managed just fine. But, I could see it being an issue for elderly or those with mobility problems.

Courtney was a doll! She was helpful in giving us menu suggestions, she was attentive and knowledgeable when we had questions. Our food was delicious and FILLING. This was a great close to our cancelled conference.
Pricey, but great steaks
Louisville restaurant deal was great. The food was very good. Melt on your mouth steaks, delicious sides excellent desserts.

Filet perfect as always. Great service, and oh those au gratin potatoes! Made my martini dirty by accident and corrected it hassle-free with subsequent perfection. Text book fine dining. Among Louisville's best.

I reserved a table for my birthday, and when we sat down we noticed they had put birthday confetti on the table and printed out keepsake menus with the date and happy birthday wishes on them. It was a very nice and thoughtful touch. The food was excellent. The wagyu meatballs were deliciously flavorful, and my lobster tail was cooked to perfection. I cannot wait to go back.
The food and service were awesome. We had a bit of a wait but it was well worth it and we were told ahead of time. Debbie was our waitress and she was great.

Food was good but I could smell what I think was old food ground into the carpet giving a foul mildewy odor and they has the lights dim enough that less than clean could be hidden, also server was a little rude.  Morton in Louisville last year dont know why google asked me to rate it now, not going back.

Awesome place to Have a Good Dinner.( Derrick) the Server was Excellent!! Checked on Us Regularly. Very Knowledgeable & a Warm Personality. Makes You feel Comfortable & @ Home...Thank You Derrick!!/Morton's🤗
The food is regularly fresh and delightful, cashiers hands over awesome customer service. I liked how neat it is and mood. Will visit here again.

We were seated in a booth near the back of the restaurant which was close to the kitchen area.  At first glance it was great to see the chefs working and food being placed on the ledge to be served.  However, it then turned very ugly and unprofessional.  We witnessed one of the chefs and the staff constantly arguing for the entire two-hour period we were there.  This atmosphere was certainly not pleasing.  It took a long time to get our main course (steaks, sides, etc.) Since we were sitting so close to the kitchen we were able to see when our food was put on the ledge to be served (Nicole was back there waiting).  Unfortunately, it sat on the ledge for nearly twenty minutes (not sure why – kitchen seemed very confused) and we watched our steaks be taken off the plate and thrown back into the oven two separate times.  Needless to say, when our food was delivered:  (i) my husband’s filet did not come with the Oscar topping as ordered so it had to be returned, and (ii) my filet came covered in a shallot butter sauce (which is not how I ordered it) (and the lady who served it to me said something like “oh, you’ll love it”).  No, I didn’t love it.  If I liked a shallot butter sauce I would have ordered it that way.  It was very disappointing that she did not even offer to take it back.  As the steaks sat on the ledge for so long so did the sides and they were not hot when they were served.  It was our first time to dine at Morton's and our last.  I would not recommend.

Very disappointing Valentine's day (Saturday) dinner.  My husband's filet was undercooked so we had to send it back. My filet was warm at best when it arrived at our table. After a couple bites I flagged down our waiter to let him know. He took it back and put it under the broiler for a minute. It was slightly better but still not that hot and was honestly a little chewy for a filet.  Positives: 1) Our server Matt was great, very friendly and attentive! 2) Side dishes were hot and flavorful. 3) They offered us free dessert, the hot chocolate cake was fabulous!  This was our first time dining at Morton's, not sure I would go again or recommend to friends.

Very disappointing Valentine's day dinner.  Negatives: 1) We were seated in what appeared to be their private dining room, off to the side of the main dining area.  Immediately upon being seated, I noticed it was very cold in this area.  I mentioned this to our waiter, he agreed that it was cold, but no remedy was offered. 2) Lobster bisque was lacking flavor. 3) My filet was undercooked and wife's was overcooked. 4) Steak temperature was warm at best when they arrived at our table and were cold shortly thereafter.  Positives: 1) Our server Graham was very informative and knowledgeable of the menu and their offerings. 2) Side dished were hot and flavorful.  This was our first time dining at Morton's, don't know that I would go again or recommend to friends.
Always good!
Nice place, my ribeye was not very good. I was very disappointed. Service was great.
A formal restaurant that provides perfect food and service.  For a wonderful experience go!
Food and service was great

Food was ok, average taste of steak. Atmosphere amazing but the two steaks we asked to put in take away boxes we not added. We learned when we got home. It was about 12 oz. of steak. With the price tag of 63.00 a piece, that was about 50.00 gone. It was a birthday dinner and we were looking forward to having this for breakfast. They gave him a birthday dessert but charged us for it, we never asked for one. 😞😞😞😞. Waited for an hour between salad an dinner. My salad had brown lettuce and had way too much vinegar for a caesar. My vegetables were cold and part of our sides came out close to the end of our meal. Very disappointing for a special event.
People at the bar are very helpful

What an incredible experience! I can honestly say I've never received such amazing service or tasted such delicious food in my life. The price certainly reflected the quality of the experience, but it was absolutely worth every penny. Our server, Tiffany, was extremely polite and professional. So glad I was able to dine here and I will gladly fork out the money to do it again.  I ordered the Prime Ribeye, Oscar Style and it was, by far, the best steak I've ever eaten.  Do yourself a favor and try this place. It's a real treat!

I had a party of 6. Seating was great. Food and orders were taken in a timely manner. I had the Cajun ribye; very nice flavor, it didn't require any steak sauce. I also had the creamed spinach and fried potato and onions both could have been seasoned better but were okay overall. For dessert I had a slice of carrot cake, it was delicious! Great customer service, very nice setting!
food was ok. expected better quality for the 45 min wait on food after order put in
Wonderful experience,  fabulous food. Debbie was a great server
Amazing

My fiancee and I went to this location to celebrate our engagement. The entire experience from the greeting to receiving the check exceeded expectations. The staff wanted to know the cause for celebration, which led to them offering to take our photo as a memory, add glitter to the table, and offer a free celebration dessert. The waitress was also very prompt and professional. A+ all around!
Excellent sea bass with an Asian flair. Nice selection of wines as well. Great service!
I've been to several Morton's but this is my favorite. Best server: Courtney... Finally got her name so we can ask for her always.

Had Christmas dinner here today, 2nd year in a row, arrived at 4pm with wife and four children ages 8 months to 17 yrs. The evening started out with appetizers taking a little longer than normal but acceptable. Dinner was the problem, it arrived beautifully at our table at 7pm In the interim the manager "Paul" intervened apologizing and informed me that dinner would be on him tonight. I eat out a lot, and usually get a robotic "I'm sorry" The food as always was phenomenal!!! Would definitely recommend for a nice dinner.
Awesome food! They personalize the menu for special occasions which is awesome!
It was ok. Eddie Merlot is better for the money
Great place to eat!

Absolutely phenomenal experience, from start to finish! The staff was absolutely lovely (shout out to our server, Courtney: she was professional but fun and made excellent recommendations, very good at her job!), I never saw anyone who looked angry or impatient. The busser stayed on top of everything, as well, and was very nice. We were greeted by Patrick, and he was also very hospitable and upbeat; he made us feel quite welcome for our first visit! The food blew us away. Indescribable. The steak was perfectly cooked and perfectly seasoned; the best steak we have ever had. The au gratin potatoes and Brussels sprouts were top notch, and the portions were big enough we took half of each home. The lobster bisque and Caesar salad were both absolutely perfect, and the layer cake was just exquisite. We will be back!

Went for my Husband's Company Christmas Party, it was the first time either of us had been to Morton's I would have given them 11stars if I could. The 4 course dinner was Amazing and the Service was Beyond Great,  they treated us like Family and were oh so friendly. Just a Wonderful and Overall Fantastic experience from the servers all the way down to the gentleman that parked my car at their Valet parking station. Their Customer Service is the Best. My only complaint was how long the wait time was between each part of the meal, but then I realized that I was with a party of nearly 50 people if not more and it takes time to prepare food for that many people as well as the Customers who were not in our Party that were dining in that evening.
The best bone-in rib eye you will ever eat

Went there for my Husband's Christmas party through his work,  it was the first time either of us had been there. The 4 course meal was delicious and the service was great. Definitely deserves 5 stars. I'd give them 8 stars if I could. The server's treat you like Family. So glad I went. Will definitely go again that's for sure.
Delicious steak and sides.  A++
Very good
Staff, food, and location are fantastic

Terrible service! Had to ask the bartender to mix my drink,  instead of taking it back to the bar he brought it to the table.  We had to ask for the table to be cleared. W was constantly looking for a server.  We waited forever for our food when it came out the lobster was over cooked and steak was cold.  The mashed potatoes was so cold we had to speak to a manager, he actually asked if it was OK to nuke them! At the end of our meal we was offered a dessert but then had to go to the bar to check out.  Total hours wasted 2 1/2. Service is everything!
Great food and great staff

Exceptional service and exquisite food prepared perfectly. Had the opportunity to try several appetizers and a taste of a couple of entrées.  Very impressive! The staff was very attentive and seemed to enjoy taking care of their patrons. My wife and I completely enjoyed our experience.

Steak is the only thing good. Sides are terrible service is more like a BW3s not a fine steakhouse. Save your money and go to a Jeff Ruby’s or hell even a longhorn steakhouse before you waste your time here. Service is simply no more than a joke.
Best steak, done to perfection.
Not worth the cost of admission in my opinion. The food was not bad but Louisville has restaurants just as good for much less money.

Never would have thought that it could be so bad.   Salad course had brown lettuce, brown avocado, generally tasteless.   All 4 steaks were luke warm when served -- at best.   The $6 truffle butter was non-existent.   All steaks were undercooked.   Asked for medium and I got rare, and cold in the center.   The only good thing was the crème brule'.
Not impressed at all, the food was ok and the service was about the same, ok. Triple the money for Apple bees level of dining.
Excellent!! Food and service both!

We came here for the first time for our anniversary and we really felt like they rolled out the red carpet for us! As soon as we walked in and told the host our name for our reservation, he congratulated us on our anniversary. We were seated at a private booth that already had our names printed on it! Next thing we knew, our host had taken a picture of us which he later turned into a nice printed keepsake for us to take home. And this was before we even met our server and got to the food! Ryan was an excellent server, very knowledgeable on the menu and very personable. We went with a lot of his recommendations and we are glad we did! The lobster bisque, filet, crab cakes, sides and desserts were all delicious--it's really hard to go wrong! Make sure you try the cream corn, truffle fries and the molten chocolate cake! We stayed until close to closing and never felt rushed. Ryan took great care of us, boxed up our leftovers, and made the whole evening a joy. Other servers also stopped by to check on us and congratulate us for the special occasion as well. They work really well as a team and we never felt neglected or overlooked. We will definitely be back, and you should definitely come here! If he's working, ask for Ryan!

I took my fiance to Morton's for his birthday. He'd never been there before. The service was phenomenal. Becca was our server, when I go back I will request her again. Her suggestions of everything was excellent just like her service. Tod was so excited that I selected this restaurant for his birthday.

We love our steakhouses and this may be one of the best we’ve been to. The staff was fun and entertaining and the bartender was lively and cute as button (if you see her talking to herself she’s not crazy, there’s someone on the other side of the window ;)). The food was perfect and hit the spot! For a nice night out, I will definitely recommend Morton’s!
Chicken is extremely bland. Customer service is wonderful.
This place was wonderful. Atmosphere was good. Staff were processional. Sitting section was good.

Service was a little slow. Usually they are on point. Food was delicious, had shrimp (grilled) and NY strip flight of steak. The Papillon Bordeaux wine was superb! The souffle took 45 min. They may have burnt it twice before getting it right. But otherwise very good for and always a pleasure t dine at Morton's!

We were celebrating our anniversary and were disappointed. Didn't have beer choice. Food came out cold,even though we were told to be careful because it just came from the oven. It took so long that we cancelled the replacement side order. The plate size was awkward and uneven and my fork slid several times into my lap. When dessert time came, they were out of our choice and it was 7 o'clock. Our server was very good but the meal was not. I have never had this experience at Morton's before.
Delicious!

My husband, 1 year old son and I came here while on vacation. The food was Phenomenal !!! And our waitress Claudia was the best waitress we’ve ever had !! She was so kind and friendly and interacted with our son it was so sweet of her ! We definitely recommend this place if your looking for a nice dinner. Would be a great place for a date night without kids also but it went good with our son!
Just wonderful being in the downtown area.

OMG. This is the Top . Can't get any better than this . All time favorite . The go above and beyond. Friends Birthday. And Put his name and Happy Birthday at Top of Menu. Happy birthday Sprinkles on table. Plus a birthday desert with a candle. And a picture of the 3 of us. This place is a top above all others. Never to be disappointed.
Food was delicious and the service was great 👌.
If food get much better, I don't know how.  Service was unbelievable!
Menu is for a big wallet as far as price. Best to make reservations. Wait staff excellent.

Morton's Steakhouse in Louisville Kentucky is one of our latest visits to a Morton's.  The staff is very well trained and attentive.  The dinning selections range from chef's seasonal selections to prime steaks & chops.  Questions are welcomed any selection.  What we did not realize is that Morton's is one of many fine restaurants throughout the US as part of Landry's Select Club.  Some of the other offers include McCormick & Schmick's and Mitchell's.  There are more Landry offerings in restaurants, gaming, hospitality and entertainment.
Incredible ambiance and good foods

Had my first meal with my wife as a married couple here around 8 months ago. I plan to make it a yearly anniversary trip. They are overwhelmingly accommodating and possibly the best place I can reccomend to eat at. I cannot wait till my next trip in a couple months!
Mmmmm good
Excellent service and food!
Went for our anniversary. They really made us feel special. Top notch food and service! Loved my filet.
Awesome
Best steak ever
Great food and servers, long wait for food
It was wonderful!!  The bar tender was awesome...

Mortons has a great product and of course the name stake to back it up. However, delay in service and missing attention to the basics has left me wondering if the juice is worth the squeeze ($$$). Upon arrival we were greeted by a friendly and professional  maître d’ and we were seated right away and were accommodated with a booth instead of a table. Our waiter was friendly and took our drink orders right away. There were a few other parties already seated but it was packed. We didn’t get our bar drinks for a while and we were told they are running behind at the bar (there was only one party in the bar area) and again it wasn’t packed. The manger brought us our bar drinks. I got one of the seasonal drinks and it was terrific and I thought it was worth the wait. Other parties began to arrive and the time between seeing our waiting and getting our bread, food or being check on by our waiter grew  longer and longer. It became noticeable that parties that had arrived after us were getting service before us (for example bar drinks). We hadn’t gotten the bread that was offered to us but later parties had gotten their bread. When we did eventually  get bread it was served by another staff member not our waiter. Dinners were severed again to people who had come in after we did. I am familiar with cook times for food and so forth but the 12 - 16 oz steaks were coming out before our 6 oz rare and medium steaks. When we did get our steak it was not served with our lobster and again by yet a different another staff member  not our waiter.  When we asked where our lobster were of course they would have to check with our waiter. No one came back. The manger who brought our bar drinks out stop by to check on us and we told him we hadn’t gotten our lobster. He said he would check on it but didn’t come back. Right around the time we were finishing up our steaks and sides our waiter came over and apologized for the lobster not coming out yet but that he would check on it. After a little bit we got our lobster however already done with the rest of our dinner. Needless to say parties that came in after us ( who ordered larger steaks) had paid, left and were going on with the rest of their Friday evening. For most working people with children it’s a lot of planning to have an evening out; getting a baby sitter, taking an Uber out and back to be disappointed. Was the juice worth the squeeze? I don’t think it was.

We had an extremely disappointing dinner.  My medium steak came out well done, as did several others at the table.  2 of us sent ours back and it was replaced with a very medium rare steak.  I don't mind paying for a good steak, but a $50 steak should be cooked perfect every time.  I wasn't about to send the steak back again so I just had it boxed up.  Their answer was a free dessert that my husband had ordered, didn't really make up for a very disapointing dinner and experience for me. On Sunday we went to Morton's for my dad's 60th birthday celebration.  Overall the food was good though nothing special, but the steaks tasted burnt and didn't seem like they were seasoned.  Texas Roadhouse and Longhorn have much better tasting food for about a third of the price.  When I got home I noticed that they had charged an extra dollar for almost every item.  Part of my bill was split with my brother, so that's why many of the items have a 1/2 next to them, but you can tell the price is higher than what our menu listed.  On Tuesday, I called the restaurant and told them that I was charged more than what our menu said.  The manager told me that they raised prices because it was Derby weekend and that they wouldn't give me a credit.  Are you kidding me?!  Their prices are outrageous to begin with for what you get, but then they have the nerve to sneak in a price increase just because of the Derby and then don't honor the prices clearly listed on the menu.  It's greedy and unethical and possibly worse.  I'll never eat at Morton's again.  Update on 6-9-19:  One of the managers reached out to me to apologize for what happened and I was sent a gift card to make up for it.  I'm changing my review from one star to three stars since they were responsive and apologetic about the situation.

Once she knew he needed a straw for everything he drank, no drink was brought out without a straw to go with it.  Debbie brought his steak for him to see, then whisked it back to the kitchen for the chef to cut it up.  Thanks to those"small" gestures, his coffee didn't taste like wine and I was able to eat with the group instead of spending so much time cutting two steaks. It made me feel a little more "normal" and a lot less stressed.  Derek (I think) was also in the room and he was a hoot--professional and fun! This is a bit of an odd review as the service was incredibly good and the food was (mostly) fantastic, and that is where I deduct a star. If 4.5 were possible I believe that would be a closer rating.  Atmosphere was nice, dimly lit, and created an all-around intimate experience.  Server was friendly and knowledgeable, aiding us in our wine selection and advising us of portion sizes with a recommendation for sharing salad course and a single side to split. I'll say those were spot on; the split salad was the proper portion and a single side is certainly plenty, but I'll get to the side in a bit.  Wife and I both had filets which were cooked to our preference (rare) with absolute perfection. It truly made the dining experience!  The single detractor from the evening was the 'twice-baked' au gratin potatoes. It seems customary at most upscale dining establishments to not include salt/pepper on the table as the food is properly seasoned and needs no changes, a decision proven correct at every other similar class restaurant I've dined at and certainly not the case here. Aside from a topping of cheese, the potatoes were devoid of any significant flavor. The addition of salt was a help but by far they were the least enjoyable part of the dining experience.  Bottom line we will definitely done here again but will under no circumstances try the twice baked au gratin potatoes!
